prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Dusk Cyan Layered Type Poster Style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules as concrete visual design constraints:
- Composition: full-bleed photographic dusk or blue-hour background, dark navy mass in the lower half, oversized title stack through the center and lower third, one huge cropped bottom word near the frame edge, small caption clusters at corners, and one circular icon badge or warm orb near the main title.
- Typography: extra-bold geometric sans headline in cyan and white, a sweeping script-style swash crossing the title, tiny all-caps microcopy, bracketed numbers, plus marks, clean side captions, and short readable poster text.
- Color: deep navy and blue-black base, bright cyan and ice white type, soft peach haze, one restrained orange accent, high contrast between warm glow and cool shadow.
- Texture and lighting: backlit blue-hour atmosphere, soft haze, matte analog print grain, crisp type edges, clean vector overlays, no uncontrolled digital noise.
- Graphic elements: thin orbital arcs, small dots, circled marks, simple arrows, bracket labels, and a flat icon silhouette related to the new subject, not mountains.

Important content rule: match the style fidelity anchors first, then change the source content. Use the new subject, new scene details, new prop, new headline, and new icon. Do not recreate the source landscape, original text, source title layout, platform UI, watermark, or mountain-sun symbol.
